Class KeyedDispatcher<Key,Receiver,Data>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.yggdrasil80.yggtools.dispatcher.keyed.KeyedDispatcher<Key,Receiver,Data>
  • Type Parameters:
    Key - The type of the key used to identify receivers, usually a String.
    Receiver - The type of the receiver, usually a listener.
    Data - The type of the data that is dispatched, usually a message, an event, etc.

    public abstract class KeyedDispatcher<Key,Receiver,Data>
extends java.lang.Object
    A dispatcher that can be used to dispatch data to multiple receivers, by key.
